{
  "texts": [
    "Especially the quasiperiodically driven system might prove to provide stable edge states robust against coherent errors.",
    "Many-body localized phases are protected by nonergodicity and the system fails to thermalize under its intrinsic dynamics.",
    "Here thermalization refers to the fact that in many-body systems any quantum states |ψ",
    "with energy E 0 will typically evolve after a certain time t to a state in which all few-body observables are well described by a thermal ensemble with a temperature determined by the energy of the initial state, allowing for a description of the system with statistical mechanics.",
    "This behavior breaks down in many-body localized phases due to disorder, which hinders thermalization similar to Anderson localization in non-interacting systems 79."
  ]
}